comment:
I was a DV advocate and I am all for believing survivors and hearing folks out, but when you have a situation where two people are allegedly abuse, and one quite reluctantly which is very common for heterosexual men, you have be more nuanced in your assessment. 

From everything that has been released it does seem like she is the perpetrator and is manipulating the situation. It’s very common for abusers, of both genders, to initiate restraining orders against the victim. Because of the power dynamic the person being abused is often the one to seek peaceful reconciliation, most victims want the relationship to continue, they just want the abuse to stop and of course that is not within their control. It’s not their fault. 

If WB didn’t want to take sides cause they don’t feel like they have the information or expertise they should have let them both go.
